problem: Improve Aver MCP tool selection efficiency without breaking compatibility
approach: Clarified tool descriptions, replaced flat MCP instructions with grouped guidance, synced README/tool docs, and added instruction-focused tests
failed_paths:
  - Editing compact schema structs in crates/aver-server/src/tools.rs was brittle with exact-match edits, so field-doc updates were limited to MCP-facing guidance changes
verification:
  - cargo fmt --all
  - cargo test -p aver-server --test mcp_instructions --test mcp_service
  - cargo clippy -p aver-server --tests -- -D warnings
workflow_learning: For compacted Rust files, prefer instruction and doc updates plus integration tests when exact-match block edits are fragile
related_files:
  - README.md
  - crates/aver-server/src/mcp.rs
  - crates/aver-server/src/scopes.rs
  - crates/aver-server/tests/mcp_service.rs
  - crates/aver-server/tests/mcp_instructions.rs
